And I don't like 55.<br>
<br>
Bjarki <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ujellah.showPublicProfile?language=EN>jellah</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>h0x0r!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(2/7/02 11:53:34 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumrantsandravesbalancingissues.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1644.topic&index=43>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: .</span><hr size=1> I am happy in the slow lane doing about 5 mph over the speed limit. I am downright thrilled to use my turn signals BEFORE I make a turn. If a car behind me wants me out of the way and is tailgating, I will be happy to get the hell out of the way. Hell if its a one lane roadway, I will pull over and let you pass, go ahead and blink your head lights at me, I will let you pass. <br>
<br>
After working claims in Geico, I just want to get to my destination alive. Thats enough for me. If the other guy thinks he owns the road, let him. I dont wish to debate it with a 2000 lb vehicle. I am sqeamish, and the sight of my own blood will simply freak me out. <p><center><img src="http://www.danos.pwp.blueyonder.co.uk/jellah.gif" width="577" height="162"></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ucubwynn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cubwynn</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_star.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>p0\/\/3r-p0sT3r!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(2/7/02 12:01:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumrantsandravesbalancingissues.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1644.topic&index=44>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.bingobear.net/jewelry.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: .</span><hr size=1> I believe you, Jellah... my ex-boyfriend works for Geico. I can't believe some of the stuff that people do on the road.<br>
