Wanderer of 51 Seasons<br>
Bears of Oboo</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/usijandistraightarrow.showPublicProfile?language=EN>sijandistraightarrow</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>p0\/\/3r-p0sT3r!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(2/9/02 5:56:01 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumrantsandravesbalancingissues.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1644.topic&index=47>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: .</span><hr size=1> LOL<br>
<br>
People are in too much of a hurry anyway. They rush thru life and then wonder where all the years went.<br>
<br>
I have 0 tolerance for anyone on the road who acts like it belongs to them alone, neither the people in a big hurry nor the dawdlers. No one _has_ to drive faster than a speed they feel safe at, unless there is a minimum speed posted.<br>
<br>
I used to be a lot more tolerant of other drivers, then I started riding a motorcycle. Try looking at that hunk of steel without a cage surrounding you, you'll feel differently about what is acceptable driving etiquette. <br>
<br>
Don't threaten me with your big hunk of steel, or you risk having me respond with little pieces of lead.<br>
<br>
Jellah is absolutely right, the most important thing is to arrive alive. People would behave differently if they ever had the opportunity to cut someone out of a crushed vehicle. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ukarbarnof.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Karbarnof </A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>p0\/\/3r-p0sT3r!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(2/9/02 8:54:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumrantsandravesbalancingissues.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1644.topic&index=48>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: .</span><hr size=1> For the last 3  years, I drive almost 600 miles a week, most of that on the interstate (routes 95 and 20). And I think I've seem more stupid shit to last me a lifetime.<br>
<br>
Yes, I do speed. Normally 10 mph above the posted speed limit. What cracks my ass is people that think that the left (passing) lane is their own personal travel lane. And are oblivious to anyone else on the road trying to get from point A to point B in a reasonable time. And what's worse is they actually get pissed off when I flash my lights or sound the horn to signal them to get the hell out of the way. Idiots, the lot of em.<br>
<br>
The others are the ones who use cruise control. Plugging along at the breakneck speed of 67 on a 65 mph stretch of highway, and decide to take 2 years to pass the JB Hunt truck in the slow lane. Now normally this wouldn't aggravate me, but when they see me coming and intentionally turn into the passing lane 2 miles before the truck. Thinking, I guess, that they might actually put their foot on either the gas or brake pedal for all of the 15 seconds it would take me to pass them.<br>
<br>
I'm not a big advocate of passing other cars while in the right hand lane. And normally will not do it unless I have to to get by these Left Lane Bandits.<br>
<br>
Its people like this that make me think I have but one nerve left and their jumping all over it.<br>
<br>
Karbarnof<br>
Oboo <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uphanttasm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Phant Tasm</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_magentaspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>p0\/\/3r-p0sT3r!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(2/9/02 9:20:15 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumrantsandravesbalancingissues.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1644.topic&index=49>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: .</span><hr size=1> &quot;People are in too much of a hurry anyway. They rush thru life and then wonder where all the years went.&quot;<br>
<br>
This is probably true, but I still want to speed, so get out of my way. <p><a href="mailto:jerryl@ameritech.net">Phant</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/udarkomen42.showPublicProfile?language=EN>DarkOmen42</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Boardaholic</span><br> <font color=#000033>(2/9/02 11:55:01 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumrantsandravesbalancingissues.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1644.topic&index=50>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: .</span><hr size=1> I get my ass out of your way as quickly as I can.<br>
<br>
I expect the same of others.<br>
<br>
It's called the Golden Rule.<br>
<br>
I want people to get out of my way, so I get out of theirs.<br>
<br>
Besides overall, I dislike driving, I like to spend as little time on the road as possible. So I speed some to get me to where I'm going even quicker. <p>Harabec Woodwalker<br>
Wanderer of 51 Seasons<br>
Bears of Oboo</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ucaederedraconis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Caedere Draconis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I live here.... get out.</span><br> <font color=#000033>(2/9/02 1:29:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumrantsandravesbalancingissues.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1644.topic&index=51>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://home.swbell.net/sdspies/images/caedphot.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: .</span><hr size=1> To road hogs:  If there's nobody in the right lane and you're not turning from the left lane, move your ass over.  Let the cops do their job and nail the speeding assholes.<br>
<br>
To the speeding assholes:  Don't be pissed when traffic isn't moving along (both lanes) as fast as you like.  If they're doing 10 over, it sounds like you have a time management problem if you can't get there on time.  Your lack of good planning does not constitute an emergency on my part.<br>
<br>
And for those who say &quot;I was on the way to the emergency room,&quot; you need to slow your ass down.  There's a reason that emergency vehicles are restricted by the speed limits.  Sure, you could save one life by hauling ass to the hospital at 90mph.  You could also take several by doing the same.  Call an ambulance if it's that critical--they can keep the person alive alot longer than you can while you're playing Gran Turismo on the road.  The only situation I can think of where you might not be able to get an ambulance is in remote locations, and when you're that far out, you wouldn't have to worry about heavy traffic anyway. <p><img src="http://home.swbell.net/sdspies/images/caederesig.jpg" BORDER="0" WIDTH="216"
